cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this template in academic work, please cite it."
title: "Control-Systems Research Template"
abstract: >-
  A MATLAB/Spyder-style Python template for academic control-systems research,
  organised around a general state-space plant abstraction (x' = f(x, u, t)) and
  AI-collaboration ready (CLAUDE.md + AGENTS.md). Stack: a Plant ABC + LTI tools,
  python-control (LQR, pole placement), cvxpy (MPC / convex optimisation), SymPy,
  and custom Runge-Kutta integrators. A Pinocchio-backed robot is the flagship
  example plant, alongside pure-NumPy plants (double integrator, mass-spring-damper,
  cart-pole).
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Jo"
    given-names: "Seonghyeon"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-06-26"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/nwilliterate/control-systems-research-template"
keywords:
